race.comment: PROCHESTER (3) looks best suited fitter and coming back in grade off a rather luckless run at Geelong. Has compelling middle-distance figures from tougher races and is ready for the step-up. TOO BIG (1) bounced straight back into the winners' stall with an easy on-pace win at Wangaratta over this distance. He will sue the inside gate and will prove tough to beat. Giving SCANDOVAL (4) an each-way chance. He raced handy placing this level at Warrnambool, and won't have to improve much to be in the finish.  KIWIESQUE (11) rated even better, narrowly missing at Kilmore over a mile. Gives every impression the middle distance will suit and she's included as well on an each-way basis.
